main event: A witness observed an object in the sky that resembled a balloon but moved much faster and exhibited a strobing effect on July 5, 1962.
interesting points: The object was visible for approximately 10 seconds., It was described as having characteristics of a balloon but behaved differently., The report concludes the sighting was probably a balloon., No photographs were included in the report., The observation type was ground-visual.
witness description: a person who saw the object
